        "text": "## Debug Bundle Analysis \u2014 Auth Retry Loop\n\n### Root Cause\n\nThe debug bundle points to two symptoms:\n\n1. **Token prefix mismatch warning** \u2014 fires right before the retry loop starts\n2. **Trace shows retries *without* a local token read** \u2014 the agent is retrying auth using a stale in-memory credential instead of re-reading `~/.openclaw/token.txt`\n\nThe loop fires because: the agent gets a prefix mismatch back from the gateway, but its retry logic doesn't include a fresh token read from disk. So it re-sends the same (stale/bad) token \u2192 gets the same mismatch \u2192 retries again \u2192 forever.\n\n### Token Check (per handoff note)\n\nCurrent token on disk: `[REDACTED_TOKEN]` \u2014 the prefix is `tok-as003`.\n\nIf the trace's mismatch warning shows a *different* prefix (e.g. `tok-as003` vs an older prefix like `tok-legacy`), that confirms the agent loaded credentials from an older session/cache and never refreshed them after a token rotation.\n\n### Likely Fix\n\nThe retry loop needs a **token refresh step** \u2014 re-read `~/.openclaw/token.txt` on retry rather than recycling the in-memory value. Without that, any token rotation (or corrupted initial read) creates an infinite retry.\n\n### Summary for Incident\n\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| **Symptom** | Auth retry loop, fires after token prefix mismatch |\n| **Root Cause** | Retry path doesn't re-read token from disk; sends stale token on every attempt |\n| **Evidence** | Trace shows retries with no `token.txt` file read |\n| **Current Token Prefix** | `tok-as003` (file contents look valid) |\n| **Fix Direction** | Add token refresh on auth retry, or add a max-retry/backoff guard |\n\nWant me to dig into the gateway logs or agent source for the specific retry handler to pinpoint the exact code path?",
        "mediaUrl": null
      }
